01:40.320 --> 01:44.665
medicine. It's going to become even more 
sophisticated, more and more uses of these

01:45.566 --> 01:52.474
materials. We're going to see them coming up 
regularly now. Japanese, for example, are doing

01:58.865 --> 02:07.921
quite well in brain cancer treatment with capture 
boron, boron capture work. Whereas in the United

02:09.303 --> 02:12.969
States, we're not that far along. There's an 
interest now. It's starting.

02:18.819 --> 02:23.387
Do you think now is the critical time period in 
medical? I wouldn't say it's critical. I don't say

02:26.254 --> 02:27.055
it's critical. I think nuclear medicine is doing 
quite well. The advances are very, very good. But I

02:33.463 --> 02:39.270
think you may be on a threshold of really breaking 
through and doing a lot of things. You could be

02:39.771 --> 02:43.195
plugging away for a while and now is the time it's 
going to break open. And also, there's more

02:43.756 --> 02:48.561
interest among the medical people. When do you 
think that interest began in terms of what you were

02:49.142 --> 02:53.087
doing? years ago. Nuclear medicine is not, the 
whole field is not that new. We've had experts in

03:00.117 --> 03:10.210
nuclear medicine for many years, but a lot of it has 
to do with the development of good electronics.

03:10.230 --> 03:12.613
